{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Spring Roll Wrappers","content":["Place flour, cornflour, 450 g water and salt in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <nobr>10 sec\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Place a small bowl on mixing bowl lid then weigh in 10 g oil and remaining 15 g water.","Heat a pancake or frying pan over a low to medium heat. Using paper towel, lightly grease pan with reserved water oil mixture. Using a silicone pastry brush, brush a paper thin layer of batter around the pan until completely covered.","Once sides are beginning to come away from pan, transfer wrapper to a plate and repeat until all batter is used.","Heat remaining 1000 g sunflower oil at a high heat (approx. 190°C) in a deep fat fryer. Meanwhile, make filling."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place carrots in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic and olive oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl then sauté <nobr>1 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, soak noodles in a bowl of boiling water.","Add sugar, fish sauce, soy sauce and oyster sauce to mixing bowl then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Remove noodles from hot water then roughly chop (3 cm) and add to mixing bowl.","Add bean sprouts, chives and reserved chopped carrots then cook <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Brush around edges of a spring roll wrapper with beaten egg. Place approx. 2 Tbsp reserved filling in a thin line on the bottom of wrapper about 2 cm from edge. Roll wrapper over filling, squeezing any air out. At the middle bring the two corners that are pointing to the side to the middle making sure they overlap. Continue to roll and tuck the top edge in and seal it with beaten egg. Repeat until all wrappers and filling are used.","Deep fry in preheated oil for approx. 5 minutes until crispy and golden brown then remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.","Serve hot with sweet chilli sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Spring Roll Wrappers","content":["150 g plain flour","90 g cornflour","465 g water","2 pinches fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["1010 g sunflower oil, for frying","70 g carrots, cut in pieces","5 garlic cloves","40 g olive oil","50 g mung bean vermicelli","2 tsp sugar","2 tsp fish sauce","2 tsp soy sauce","40 g oyster sauce","150 g soy bean sprouts, fresh","10 fresh chives, cut in lengths (3 cm)","1 medium egg, beaten","20 g sweet chilli sauce, or as desired, to serve"]}],"id":"r104811","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-Pa1KQ_I2lH4\/XZWaIerh9NI\/AAAAAAAAeW8\/SGyoI1vVnsEjuGG5aknGj7MH2UkwlcQgQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_yrG5IZPMr4AOSt11.png","title":"Vegetable Spring Rolls","publishedAt":"2016-04-25T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.1 g","fat":"3.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"21.1 g","calories":"521 kJ \/ 125 kcal"},"usefulItems":"paper towel, pastry brush, pancake pan or frying pan, deep saucepan or deep fat fryer, slotted spoon, hob","hintsAndTricks":["It is difficult to find spring roll wrappers suitable for frying authentic spring rolls in UK and Irish supermarkets which is why we make them from scratch using the Thermomix®."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h 50m","2h 10m","14 portions"]}